hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: We need someone with experience healthful-pills.com Lionhead originally joined Microsoft because it didn't have the resources to fund the games it wanted to make, Carr continued. "I think Lionhead was at the point where it wanted to be acquired, so that it could move onto the next phase. We could see where it was going, and how expensive game development was becoming, and the reality was that we were trying to stay at the triple-A, high-end development edge, and that was because we'd evolved to that point.
